      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TOO BUSY (1) tends to drift back and work into the race, finishing out of the placings two back before charging home into the minors latest when third (16.33) in a Grade 5 at this track last time. Has a good record at this journey. Comes out of a solid form race last start. One of the leading chances. CAKE IN TUMMY (2) scored well last start as odds-on favourite by 1.75 lengths at this track in a handy 16.29 beating Mayday Mayday. Draws to advantage and in form and has the ability. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in her latest win. Can make it back-to-back wins. LITTLE DITZY (4) collided in the run and missed the frame when sixth (22.99) at Mandurah over 400m in a Grade 5. Has the ability and can atone with the right run. ELITE EMU (3) is in the mix despite missing out at this track last time.",
